Pandas, NumPy â€“ Data handling

ğŸ“ Dataset Overview
File: train.txt
Format: Semicolon-separated (;)
Columns:
Text: The sentence/text sample
Emotions: The emotion label (e.g., joy, fear, sadness)

ğŸ”„ Preprocessing Steps
Tokenization â€“ Convert text to sequences of integers
Padding â€“ Normalize input length for model input
Label Encoding â€“ Convert emotion labels to numeric
One-hot Encoding â€“ For multi-class classification

ğŸ§  Model Architecture
Embedding Layer â€“ Word vector representations
Flatten Layer
Dense Layer (ReLU)
Output Layer (Softmax for multi-class classification)

ğŸ”§ Training
Loss: categorical_crossentropy
Optimizer: adam
Epochs: 10
Batch Size: 32
Final Accuracy: ~99.7% (train) and ~82.9% (validation)

ğŸ§ª Sample Prediction
